headline: Ares (ARES) Stock Trades Up, Here Is Why
summary: Shares of alternative asset manager Ares Management (NYSE:ARES) jumped 8.5% in the afternoon session after reports revealed the company was set to be included in the S&P 500 index. S&P Dow Jones Indices announced that Ares Management would replace Kellanova in the benchmark index before the market opened on December 11. headline: Ares Stock Surges. It Went From S&P 500 Snub to Kellanova Sub.
summary: Ares, with a market capitalization of $54 billion, is one of the largest companies by market value not currently in the S&P 500.  It was one of the top candidates for inclusion in the S&P 500 when the index made its rebalancing announcement on Friday.  Carvana CRH  and  Comfort Systems USA  got the go-ahead, while Ares was snubbed.
